panels.description: The percentage of CPU utilization.
panels.title: CPU Utilization by Node

panels.description: The amount of free memory available on the host.
panels.title: Freeable  Memory by Node

panels.description: The number of bytes the host has read from the network and the number of bytes the host has written to the network.
panels.title: Network Bytes In & Out by Node

panels.description: A count of the number of connections connected to the cache at an instant in time. ElastiCache uses two to three of the connections to monitor the cluster in each case.
panels.title: Current Connections by Cluster

panels.description: The number of new connections the cache has received. This is derived from the memcached total connections statistic by recording the change in total connections across a period of time. This will always be at least 1, due to a connection reserved for a ElastiCache.
panels.title: New Connections by Cluster

panels.description: The number of Cas requests the cache has received where the requested key was found and the Cas value matched.
panels.title: Cas Hits & Misses by Cluster

panels.description: The number of get commands the cache has received.
panels.title: Get Commands by Cluster

panels.description: The number of set commands the cache has received.
panels.title: Set Commands by Cluster

panels.description: The number of get commands the cache has received.
panels.title: Get Commands by Cluster

panels.description: The number of set commands the cache has received.
panels.title: Set Commands by Cluster

panels.description: The number of flush commands the cache has received.
panels.title: Flush Commands by Cluster

panels.description: The total number of slab pages that have been moved.
panels.title: Slabs Moved by Cluster

panels.description: The number of bytes used to store cache items.
panels.title: Bytes Used for Cache Items by Cluster

panels.description: The number of bytes used to store cache items.
panels.title: Bytes Used for Cache Items by Node

panels.description: The number of bytes currently used by hash tables.
panels.title: Bytes Used For Hash by Cluster

panels.description: The amount of swap used on the host.
panels.title: Swap Usage by Cluster

panels.description: The amount of swap used on the host.
panels.title: Swap Usage by Node

panels.description:
The amount of memory not used by data. This is derived from the Memcached statistics limit maxbytes and bytes by subtracting bytes from limit maxbytes.

Because Memcached overhead uses memory in addition to that used by data, UnusedMemory should not be considered to be the amount of memory available for additional data. You may experience evictions even though you still have some unused memory.
panels.title: Unused Memory by Cluster

panels.description: The number of get requests the cache has received where the key requested was found and the number of get requests the cache has received where the key requested was not found.
panels.title: Get Hits & Misses By Bluster

panels.description: The number of increment requests the cache has received where the key requested was found and the number of increment requests the cache has received where the key requested was not found.
panels.title: Increment Hits and Misses by Cluster

panels.description: The number of decrement requests the cache has received where the requested key was found and the number of decrement requests the cache has received where the requested key was not found.
panels.title: Decrement Hits & Misses by Cluster

panels.description: The number of delete requests the cache has received where the requested key was found and the number of delete requests the cache has received where the requested key was not found.
panels.title: Delete Hits & Misses by Cluster

panels.description: The number of keys that have been touched and were given a new expiration time and the number of items that have been touched, but were not found.
panels.title: Touch Hits & Misses by Cluster

panels.description: The current number of configurations stored.
panels.title: Current Config by Cluster

panels.description: The cumulative number of config get requests and the cumulative number of config set requests.
panels.title: Config Get & Set Requests by Cluster

panels.description: The cumulative number of touch requests.
panels.title: Touch Requests by Cluster

panels.description: The number of CAS (check and set) requests the cache has received where the Cas value did not match the Cas value stored.
panels.title: CAS Bad Value by Cluster

panels.description: A count of the number of items currently stored in the cache.
panels.title: Current Items by Cluster

panels.description: The number of new items the cache has stored. This is derived from the memcached total items statistic by recording the change in total items across a period of time.
panels.title: New Items by Cluster

panels.description: The number of expired items the cache evicted to allow space for new writes.
panels.title: Reclaimed by Cluster

panels.description: The number of valid items evicted from the least recently used cache (LRU) which were never touched after being set.
panels.title: Evicted Unfetched by Cluster

panels.description: The number of expired items reclaimed from the LRU which were never touched after being set.
panels.title: Expired Unfetched by Cluster

panels.description: The number of non-expired items the cache evicted to allow space for new writes.
panels.title: Evictions by Cluster

panels.description: The number of bytes that have been read from the network by the cache node the number of bytes that have been written to the network by the cache node.
panels.title: Bytes Read In and Out of MemCached by Cluster

panels.description: The number of packets received and sent from and too all network interfaces by the instance. This metric identifies the volume of incoming and outgoing traffic in terms of the number of packets on a single instance.
panels.title: Network Packets In & Out by Node
